Genetic C++ library (libgen) README
===================================


0. Contents
-------------------------
1. About
2. How to build


1. About
-------------------------

The libgen genetic library provides a C++ implementation for general
purpose genetic algorithms.

For now the documentation will be found throughout the code and it is
rather scarce, but this will be improved in the future.

The library allows using genetic algorithms to solve any problem
provided that:
* it can be encoded on "chromosomes" (genotype / phaenotype conversion)
* phaenotypes have a well defined "fitness" function


2. How to build
-------------------------

To build, the following are required:
* gcc
* make

The Makefile provides targets for building the library (libgen). Running

	make

will build the library and the unit tests, and will run the unit tests.
